HEADWORD: Two-lipped
<hw>Two"-lipped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having two lips.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Divided in such a manner as to
resemble the two lips when the mouth is more or less open;
bilabiate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Two-name</ent>⟦br⟧
